nd2|{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n<!--All columns are for the 2019 election. See [[Parliamentary constituencies in Hertfordshire]] if you have trouble with the \"Member of Parliament\" and \"Nearest opposition\" columns.-->\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=1|Constituency<ref group=nb>BC denotes borough constituency, CC denotes county constituency.</ref>\n!rowspan=1|Electorate\n!rowspan=1|Majority<ref group=nb>The majority is the number of votes the winning candidate receives more than their nearest rival.</ref>\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|[[Member of Parliament]]\n!colspan=2 class=unsortable|Nearest opposition\n<!--!rowspan=1 class=unsortable|Electoral wards<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.opsi.gov.uk/si/si2007/uksi_20071681_en_4|title=The Parliamentary Constituencies (England) Order 2007, page 4|publisher=Crown copyright|work=[[Office of Public Sector Information]]|accessdate=7 November 2009|date=13 June 2007}}</ref><ref>[[Boundary Commissions (United Kingdom)|Boundary Commission for England]] pp. 1004\u20131007</ref> -->\n!rowspan=1 class=unsortable|Map\n|-\n|[[Chippenham (UK Parliament constituency)|Chippenham CC]]\n|76,432\n|11,288\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|[[Michelle Donelan]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|[[Helen Belcher]]\n|[[Image:Chippenham2007Constituency.svg|left|100px|alt=]]\n|-\n|[[Devizes (UK Parliament constituency)|Devizes CC]]\n|72,184\n|23,993\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|[[Danny Kruger]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|Jo Waltham\n|[[Image:Devizes2007Constituency.svg|left|100px|alt=]]\n|-\n|[[North Swindon (UK Parliament constituency)|North Swindon CC]]\n|80,168\n|16,171\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|[[Justin Tomlinson]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|Kate Linnegar\n|[[Image:NorthSwindon2007Constituency.svg|left|100px|alt=]]\n|-\n|[[North Wiltshire (UK Parliament constituency)|North Wiltshire CC]]\n|71,408\n|17,626\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|[[James Gray (British politician)|James Gray]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|Brian Matthew\n|[[Image:NorthWiltshire2007Constituency.svg|left|100px|alt=]]\n|-\n|[[Salisbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Salisbury CC]]\n|72,892\n|19,736\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|[[John Glen (politician)|John Glen]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|Victoria Charleston\n|[[Image:Salisbury2007Constituency.svg|left|100px|alt=]]\n|-\n|[[South Swindon (UK Parliament constituency)|South Swindon CC]]\n|72,372\n|6,625\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|[[Robert Buckland]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|Sarah Church\n|[[Image:SouthSwindon2007Constituency.svg|left|100px|alt=]]\n|-\n|[[South West Wiltshire (UK Parliament constituency)|South West Wiltshire CC]]\n|76,898\n|21,630\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|[[Andrew Murrison]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n|Emily Pomroy-Smith\n|[[Image:SouthWestWiltshire2007Constituency.svg|left|100px|alt=]]\n|}\n\n==Boundary changes==\n'''Previous constituency boundaries'''\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" \n|-\n!bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"|Name!!bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"|Pre-2010 Boundaries\n|-\n|\n# [[Devizes (UK Parliament constituency)|Devizes CC]]\n# [[North Swindon (UK Parliament constituency)|North Swindon CC]]\n# [[North Wiltshire (UK Parliament constituency)|North Wiltshire CC]]\n# [[Salisbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Salisbury CC]]\n# [[South Swindon (UK Parliament constituency)|South Swindon CC]]\n# [[Westbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Westbury CC]]\n|[[Image:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituenciesNumbered.svg|left|Parliamentary constituencies in Wiltshire]]\n|-\n|}\n\n'''Current constituency boundaries'''\n<ref>\nThe [[Boundary Commission for England]] recommended that the county should be\ndivided into seven constituencies.\nThese changes were implemented at the [[2010 United Kingdom general election]].</ref>\n{| border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" \n|-\n!bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"|Name!!bgcolor=\"#ff9999\"|New boundaries\n|-\n|\n# [[Chippenham (UK Parliament constituency)|Chippenham CC]]\n# [[Devizes (UK Parliament constituency)|Devizes CC]]\n# [[North Swindon (UK Parliament constituency)|North Swindon CC]]\n# [[North Wiltshire (UK Parliament constituency)|North Wiltshire CC]]\n# [[Salisbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Salisbury CC]]\n# [[South Swindon (UK Parliament constituency)|South Swindon CC]]\n# [[South West Wiltshire (UK Parliament constituency)|South West Wiltshire CC]]\n|[[Image:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituencies2007.svg|left|Proposed Revision]]\n|-\n|}\n\n== Proposed boundary changes ==\nThe [[Boundary Commission for England]] submitted their final proposals in respect of the [[Sixth Periodic Review of Westminster constituencies|Sixth Periodic Review of Westminster Constituencies]] (the 2018 review) in September 2018. Although the proposals were immediately laid before [[Parliament of the United Kingdom|Parliament]] they were not brought forward by the [[Government of the United Kingdom|Government]] for approval. Accordingly, they '''did''' '''not''' come into effect for the [[2019 United Kingdom general election|2019 election]] which took place on 12 December 2019, and which was contested using the constituency boundaries in place since 2010.\n\nUnder the terms of the [[Parliamentary Voting System and Constituencies Act 2011]], the Sixth Review was based on reducing the total number of MPs from 650 to 600 and a strict electoral parity requirement that the electorate of all constituencies should be within a range of 5% either side of the electoral quota.\n\nOn 24 March 2020, the Minister of State for the [[Cabinet Office]], [[Chloe Smith]], issued a written statement to Parliament setting out the Government's thinking with regard to parliamentary boundaries. They propose to bring forward [[Primary and secondary legislation|primary legislation]] to remove the statutory obligation to implement the 2018 Boundary Review recommendations, as well as set the framework for future boundary reviews in time for the next review which is due to begin in early 2021 and report no later than October 2023. It is proposed that the number of constituencies now remains at the current level of 650, rather than being reduced to 600, while retaining the requirement that the electorate should be no more than +/- 5% from the electoral quota.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2020-03-24/HCWS183/|title=Update: Strengthening Democracy:Written statement - HCWS183|website=UK Parliament|language=English|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"288\">\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency1979Results.svg|'''1974 Feb'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency1979Results.svg|'''1974 Oct'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency1979Results.svg|'''1979'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency1992Results.svg|'''1983'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency1992Results.svg|'''1987'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency1992Results.svg|'''1992'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency2005Results.svg|'''1997'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency2005Results.svg|'''2001'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency2005Results.svg|'''2005'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency2010Results.svg|'''2010'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency2017Results.svg|'''2015'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency2017Results.svg|'''2017'''\nFile:WiltshireParliamentaryConstituency2017Results.svg|'''2019'''\n</gallery>\n\n==Historical representation by party==\nA cell marked \u2192 (with a different colour background to the preceding cell) indicates that the previous MP continued to sit under a new party name.\n\n===1885 to 1918===\n{{legend2|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}|[[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n{{legend2|{{Liberal Unionist Party/meta/color}}|[[Liberal Unionist Party|Liberal Unionist]]|border=1px solid #aaaaaa}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Constituency\n!1885\n!1886\n!1892\n!1895\n!''97''\n!''98''\n!''00''\n!1900\n!''05''\n!1906\n!Jan 1910\n!Dec 1910\n!''11''\n!''18''\n|-\n|[[Westbury (UK Parliament constituency)|Westbury]]\n| colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[George Fuller (British politician)|Fuller]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" colspan=\"4\" |[[Richard Chaloner, 1st Baron Gisborough|Chaloner]]\n| colspan=\"5\" bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Sir John Fuller, 1st Baronet|Fuller]]\n| colspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Geoffrey Howard (Liberal politician)|Howard]]\n|-\n|[[Cricklade (UK Parliament constituency)|Cricklade]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Nevil Story Maskelyne|Maskelyne]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Unionist Party/meta/color}}\" |[[Nevil Story Maskelyne|\u2192]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[John Husband|Husband]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Unionist Party/meta/color}}\" colspan=\"2\" |[[Alfred Hopkinson|Hopkinson]]\n| colspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[Edmond FitzMaurice, 1st Baron FitzMaurice|FitzMaurice]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[John Massie|Massie]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Unionist Party/meta/color}}\" |[[Thomas Charles Pleydell Calley|Calley]]\n| colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"{{Liberal Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |[[